      "content": "Let's get into the specifics. When it comes to Black urban style, you're looking at a blend of 80s and 90s influences, with a focus on bold graphics, bright colors, and oversized silhouettes. Think baggy jeans, oversized shirts, and gold chains. Unspoken rules include:\n\n* Avoid using African American models or imagery that's too \"ghetto\" or \"urban\" - you want to focus on the fashion, not the community.\n* Incorporate elements like graffiti, street art, and bold typography to give your design a \"raw\" edge.\n* Don't be afraid to mix and match different patterns and textures, like stripes with polka dots.\n\nFor Latinx urban style, you're looking at a more vibrant, eclectic mix of influences. Think:\n\n* Bright colors, bold graphics, and playful patterns like Aztec or Day of the Dead-inspired designs.\n* Incorporate elements like chunky jewelry, layered necklaces, and chunky sneakers.\n* Don't be afraid to mix high-end and low-end fashion, like pairing luxury brands with thrift store finds.\n\nAs for Asian American urban style, it's all about blending traditional and modern elements. Think:\n\n* Incorporate traditional Asian motifs like cherry",
